{"name": "appnope", "metadata": {"name": "appnope", "version": "0.1.4", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: MacOS :: MacOS X", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "http://github.com/minrk/appnope", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Disable App Nap on macOS >= 10.9", "upload_time": 1707212589}, "documentation": ["# `appnope`\n\nSimple package for disabling App Nap on macOS >= 10.9,\nwhich can be problematic.\n\nTo disable App Nap:\n\n```python\nimport appnope\nappnope.nope()\n```\n\nTo reenable, for some reason:\n\n```python\nappnope.nap()\n```\n\nor to only disable App Nap for a particular block:\n\n```\nwith appnope.nope_scope():\n    do_important_stuff()\n```\n\nIt uses ctypes to wrap a `[NSProcessInfo beginActivityWithOptions]` call to disable App Nap.\n\nTo install:\n\n    pip install appnope\n"], "modules": [{"name": "appnope", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "appnope._v", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "version_s", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "appnope.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "appnope._dummy", "documentation": ["-----------------------------------------------------------------------------", "Copyright (C) 2013 Min RK", "Distributed under the terms of the 2-clause BSD License.", "-----------------------------------------------------------------------------"], "functions": [{"name": "appnope._dummy.beginActivityWithOptions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "options", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reason", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "appnope._dummy.endActivity", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "activity", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "appnope._dummy.nope", "asynchronou